               <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en">Test on a subset and assess quality</head>
               <desc xml:lang="en" type="definition">
                  <p>The first step to take is the definition of a
              target accuracy. <list>
                        <item>Clean printed text: WER 70% is a minimum (can be 60% for a search
                  engine)</item>
                        <item>HTR of badly printed: The acceptable WER may be less. Then again, it depends
                  on the outcomes.</item>
                     </list>
                  </p>
                  <p>To test the accuracy of the model, two metrics are available: Character Error rate
              (CER) and Word Error rate (WER). WER is more important because it defines the
              readability of the text. It is also important to assess the quality of the layout
              recognition.</p>
               </desc>
